      • enableDebug

        public static void enableDebug()

      • enableDebug

        public static void enableDebug(int level)

      • dispose

        public void dispose()

      • available

        public boolean available()
        Returns whether there is a new frame waiting to be displayed.

      • read

        public void read()
        Loads the most recent frame available. After calling this method, you can use the object like any PImage, e.g. by using the image function to draw it to the screen.

      • play

        public void play()
        Starts or resumes video playback. The play method will play a video file till the end and then stop. GLVideo objects start out paused, so you might want to call this method, or loop.

      • loop

        public void loop()
        Starts or resumes looping video playback. The loop method will continuously play back a video file. GLVideo objects start out paused, so you might want to call this method, or play.

      • playing

        public boolean playing()
        Returns true if the video is playing or if playback got interrupted by buffering.

      • noLoop

        public void noLoop()
        Stops a looping video after the end of its current iteration.

      • jump

        public void jump(float sec)
        Jumps to a specific time position in the video file.
        Parameters:
        sec - seconds from the start of the video

      • speed

        public void speed(float rate)
        Changes the speed in which a video file plays. Values larger than 1.0 will play the video faster than real time, while values lower than 1.0 will play it slower. Values less or equal than zero are currently not supported.
        Parameters:
        rate - playback rate (1.0 is real time)

      • volume

        public void volume(float vol)
        Changes the volume of the video's audio track, if there is one.
        Parameters:
        vol - (0.0 is mute, 1.0 is 100%)

      • pause

        public void pause()
        Pauses a video file. Playback can be resumed with the play or loop methods.

      • duration

        public float duration()
        Returns the total length of the movie file in seconds.

      • time

        public float time()
        Returns the current time position in seconds.

      • width

        public int width()
        Returns the native width of the movie file in pixels.

      • height

        public int height()
        Returns the native height of the movie file in pixels.

      • frameRate

        public float frameRate()
        Returns the native frame rate of the movie file in frames per second (fps). This is currently not implemented.

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes a movie file. This method releases all resources associated with the playback of a movie file. Call close before loading and playing back a second file. After calling close no other methods can be used anymore on this GLVideo instance.
